    public class LexakaiProject
extends com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.messaging.repeaters.BaseRepeater
implements java.lang.Comparable<LexakaiProject>
    Represents a project for which Lexakai is producing diagrams.

    Java Parsing

    The project has types that are discovered using the JavaParser API. Those types are available through typeDeclarations() and typeDeclarations(Consumer).

    Settings

    Projects have various settings that are used to define how the UML for a project is generated. These settings are configured by the Lexakai application from the command line.

    • addHtmlAnchors(boolean)
    • automaticMethodGroups(boolean)
    • buildPackageDiagrams(boolean)
    • includeObjectMethods(boolean)
    • includeProtectedMethods(boolean)
    • javadocSectionPattern(Pattern)

    Functions

    These methods produce user-facing results for the Lexakai application:

    • diagrams(Consumer) - Produces UML diagram(s) for the project
    • nestedProjectJavadocCoverage() - Determines Javadoc coverage for types in the project
    • updateReadMe() - Updates the indexing in README.md for the project
    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
